OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FHarvard removes human skin 
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fbinding from book          
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Harvard University has removed the     
OL,6, binding of human skin from a 19th      
OL,7, Century book kept in its library.      
OL,9,FDes Destinees de l'Ame (Destinies of   
OL,10,Fthe Soul) has been housed at Houghton  
OL,11,FLibrary since the 1930s.               
OL,13,FIn 2014, scientists determined that the
OL,14,Fmaterial it was bound with was in fact 
OL,15,Fhuman skin.                            
OL,17,FBut the university has now announced it
OL,18,Fhas removed the binding "due to the    
OL,19,Fethically fraught nature of the book's 
OL,20,Forigins and subsequent history".       
